TITLE: Enough! French police unions condemn 'savage hordes,' forcing Macron into action
SUMMARY: Defying all odds against overwhelming numbers of rioters, French police officers are curtailing the violence and have compelled the French political establishment to stand behind them.

TITLE: South Korea draws hard line on North Korean aid, no longer a 'support department' for dictatorship
SUMMARY: South Korea ordered its Unification Ministry to shift its directives away from "support" for North Korea toward combatting its human rights abuses.

TITLE: Syria claims to shoot down Israeli missile strike as anti-aircraft debris lands in Israeli town
SUMMARY: Syria claims to have shot down Israeli missiles targeting air defense batteries near the city of Hom, with Israel saying no warplanes were damaged.

TITLE: Ukrainian officials report drone strikes shot down over Kyiv
SUMMARY: Officials in Kyiv, Ukraine, reported a wave of drone strikes against the city late Saturday into Sunday that were intercepted and failed to hit the city.

TITLE: Mexican government laments DeSantis immigration laws, warns of 'discrimination' and 'racial profiling'
SUMMARY: The Mexican government released a statement Saturday harshly criticizing Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis's latest immigration bill, which went into effect Friday.

TITLE: World's largest croc still growing as it hits stunning age milestone: experts
SUMMARY: Cassius was captured near the city of Darwin in 1984 and three years later transferred to the Green Island croc park, where he's remained happy and healthy for decades.

TITLE: France protests show first signs of subsiding after tens of thousands of police confront 5th night of violence
SUMMARY: Violent protests continued in France, as thousands of police officials worked to contain demonstrations that finally began to subside after nearly a week.

TITLE: Human rights advocates raise alarm over persecution of Indian Christians amid Modi's US visit
SUMMARY: Human rights advocates are raising the alarm about the rising persecution of Christians in India amid Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi's recent visit to the United States.

TITLE: Pence calls on Biden to 'cease and desist' nuclear negotiations with Iran
SUMMARY: Former Vice President Mike Pence on Saturday called on President Biden to "cease and desist" all negotiations with Iran, calling pursuit of a nuclear deal "ill-founded and dangerous."

TITLE: French riots: What to know as hundreds of police hurt, thousands of protesters arrested after deadly shooting
SUMMARY: President Macron has blamed social media among other things for stoking the violence that has spread across France for four days after the shooting death of a teenager.

TITLE: Macron dances at Elton John concert as France burns amid ongoing violence
SUMMARY: The protests have spread from Paris, where the initial shooting occurred, to other towns across the country, though most of the violence remains localized to the Paris suburbs.

TITLE: At least 51 killed in horrifying wreck in Kenya, 32 injured, authorities and Red Cross say
SUMMARY: A horrific traffic accident in western Kenya left at least 51 people dead and 32 more injured after a truck lost control and slammed into six other vehicles in a busy market.

TITLE: Wagner boss Prigozhin shutters his 'Patriot Media' operations
SUMMARY: Wagner mercenary boss Yevgeny Prigozhin is reportedly shutting down his Russian media holdings following his short-lived rebellion. The reports first emerged on Friday.

TITLE: Child, 7, plummets from ferry to his death; mother dies trying to save him
SUMMARY: A murder investigation has been opened after a boy, 7, and his mother are dead after falling off a ferry traveling from Sweden to Poland, Swedish authorities said.

TITLE: Over 1,300 arrested across France during fourth night of riots sparked by police killing of teen
SUMMARY: Over 1,300 people were arrested across France Friday night and into Saturday morning following chaotic riots in response to the police killing of 17-year-old Nahel M.

TITLE: France deploys thousands of police officers amid riots, hundreds arrested
SUMMARY: French officials are deploying 45,000 police officers amid a fourth night of riots stemming from a fatal shooting involving a police officer.

TITLE: Mexican family of 6-year-old boy who fell from amusement park zipline to file lawsuit
SUMMARY: The family of a 6-year-old boy in Mexico whose zip line harness broke at an amusement park is filing a lawsuit, according to a family source.

TITLE: Biden admin denies 'interim' Iran deal, but new report suggests continued diplomatic backdoor dealings
SUMMARY: The Biden administration has claimed there is no nuclear deal "in the offing," but recent reports indicate that U.S. and Iranian officials have continued diplomatic talks.

TITLE: Madeleine McCann witness claims suspect in her kidnapping drunkenly confessed to crime
SUMMARY: A German man with apparent information about Madeleine McCann's disappearance told a newspaper this week that suspect Christian Brueckner had confessed to kidnapping her.

TITLE: Bolsonaro banned from running for office for 8 years
SUMMARY: Former Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro is banned from seeking public office for eight years, preventing him from launching a political campaign until 2030.

TITLE: Thousands of protesters rally across Iraq for a 2nd day to condemn the burning of a Quran in Sweden
SUMMARY: Protests continued for a second day in Iraq over the burning of a Quran in Sweden. Some called on Iraqi authorities to expel the Swedish ambassador.

TITLE: Taiwanese foreign minister claims China repeating 'origin of the second World War'
SUMMARY: Taiwan Foreign Minister Joseph Wu speculated that the People's Republic of China could accidentally spark a third World War with its ongoing aggression.

TITLE: Popular tourist destination wants total suitcase ban as travel surges post-pandemic
SUMMARY: The Dubrovnik Travel Board is working on a system to transport suitcases from airports directly to travelers' local addresses while they stay in the popular Croatian city.

TITLE: Research trip in Mexico tragically cut short after UC Berkeley PhD student gets fatally shot 7 times
SUMMARY: A University of California, Berkeley, Ph.D. student who was studying a flowering shrub across North America was found dead in Mexico where his body was shot seven times.

TITLE: Out-of-control paraglider barrels into shop roof as shocked onlookers watch: video
SUMMARY: A paragliding tourist in Thailand crashes a festival after losing control and landing on top of an outdoor market's roof.
